Project 01 — Empathy Map & User Persona

Type:UX Research  
Tool:Figma  
Figma Link:https://www.figma.com/design/glRtMJ7INB8JTUZz46k0xg/DECODE_LABS_PROJECTS?node-id=1-5730&t=tpMFyPmpUhNNIMKs-0

#Scenario
A fitness startup needed an app for busy office professionals who struggle to find time for exercise. Before designing anything, the goal was to deeply understand the user's 
pain points.

#What I Did
- Analyzed the target user: a time-poor professional with 
  a 40+ hour work week
- Created a User Persona with age range 25-40, occupation, 
  goals, and frustrations
- Built a 4-Quadrant Empathy Map covering: Says, Thinks, 
  Feels, and Does
- Identified 3 core friction points: workouts too long, 
  apps too gamified, gym dependency

#Key Insight
Designed for the user who cannot leave their desk — not the user who lives at the gym. Focused on micro-workout solutions and desk exercises.
